    "An IRBO score of 0 indicates identical topics, while a score of 1 indicates completely different topics [85].We believe that the combination of coherence and diversity metrics provides a more comprehensive evaluation of topic models and can help researchers to make informed decisions about which models to use for their specific applications.Table 1 Best evaluation scores obtained on the datasets for flat topic detection The best results are in bold Models Datasets C V C NPMI PUW PJD IRBO Time (seconds) CT BBC 0.700 0.170 1 1 1 2.786 NG20 0.769 0.166 1 1 1 5.060 Reuters 0.690 0.107 1 1 1 4.051 EuroParl 0.535 0.044 1 1 1 1.384 LDA BBC 0.461 -0.028 0.460 0.605 0.353 6.49 NG20 0.552 0.038 0.800 0.9133 0.8663 4.53 Reuters 0.453 0.002 0.620 0.796 0.580 5.32 EuroParl 0.463 -0.009 0.860 0.957 0.927 3.990 Top2Vec BBC 0.630 0.043 1 1 1 16.98 NG20 0.655 0.082 0.637 0.966 0.998 62.47 Reuters 0.686 0.158 0.473 0.923 0.996 55.53 EuroParl 0.285 -0.482 1 1 1 92.71 BerTopic BBC 0.550 0.041 0.504 0.767 0.843 309.592 NG20 0.784 0.165 0.795 0.997 0.998 1436.311 Reuters 0.823 0.250 0.682 0.997 0.998 1620.018 EuroParl 0.75 0.128 0.746 0.998 0.998 473.070 CorEx BBC 0.603 -0.023 1 1 1 62.634 NG20 0.518 0.032 1 1 1 65.580 Reuters 0.605 0.051 1 1 1 64.695 EuroParl 0.314 -0.172 1 1 1 39.441 13 https:// github.",
